# eGymSystem Codegen Root Rule

Use this rule first, then follow child rule by target area:

- Backend target -> follow `market-backend-structure.mdc` scoped to `eGymSystem.Backend`
- Frontend target -> follow `market-frontend-structure.mdc` scoped to `eGymSystem.Frontend`
- API contract change -> follow both backend + frontend rules and `market-contract-sync.mdc`

Hard constraints:

- Keep existing folder architecture. Do not invent new top-level architecture style.
- Keep naming style already used in repo.
- Prefer minimal diff touching smallest valid layer set.
- For feature work, create/modify tests in corresponding test area.
- Hard guard: do not generate or modify code under `Market.Backend` or `Market.Frontend`.
- Hard guard: all new work targets `eGymSystem.Backend` and `eGymSystem.Frontend` only.
- For vault task tracking, use status model: `TODO`, `DOING`, `PARTIAL`, `BLOCKED`, `DONE`.
- Parent task status rule: set `DONE` only when all child + parent checklist items are complete; otherwise use `PARTIAL`.
- Parent execution rule (mandatory): for each parent phase (ex: C1.1-C1.10), complete every item in the parent `.md` first, then mark parent `PARTIAL`, then continue to next parent phase.
- Setup-mode rule: when user asks "setup/scaffold only", generate contracts, endpoints, route shells, and wiring only; return `501 Not Implemented`/placeholders for business logic.
